ica, but with the development of a new rear-wheel drive sports car, the automakers image may be jeopardized. This is an issue that has Subarus management worried, so much so that it is even considering...\r\n    \r\n...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/MotorAuthority/~3/l2_nC6xcbb0/1040527_subaru-unsure-of-bringing-rwd-sports-car-to-u-s\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>','Subaru Unsure Of Bringing RWD Sports Car To U.S.  '),(3714,'0','2009-12-21 10:05:00','<img src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com/uk.autoblog.com/media/2009/12/saab_95.jpg\" alt=\"\" />Filed under: GM, Saab, Spyker, News \r\nGeneral Motors pulled the plug on Saab over the weekend, after talks over a deal with Spyker broke down. \r\nIn a press conference shortly after the announcement to close the Swedish company, GM Vice president of Corporate Planning John Smith cited \"unresolvable issues\" on both sides, as the reason for the decision. He did confim however that the decision was not due to a lack of financial support from the Swedish Government or the European Investment Bank, although it is understood that its refusal to act as an investor made the task to save Saab much harde...<br><a href=\"http://uk.autoblog.com/2009/12/21/gm-kills-off-saab-but-spyker-revises-offer/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: uk.autoblog.com</a><br>','GM kills off Saab, but Spyker revises offer'),(3715,'0','2009-12-21 15:00:00','<img src=\"http://img.worldcarfans.com/2009/12/23648.tn.jpg\" alt=\"http://img.worldcarfans.com/2009/12/23648.tn.jpg\" /> Two days after GM announced Saab would be closed, Spyker has submitted a new 11-point bid for the company.\r\n \r\n...<br><a href=\"http://feeds.worldcarfans.com/~r/worldcarfans/Jxfz/~3/63mB8pr8vnU/saab-not-dead-yet--spyker-makes-new-offer\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feeds.worldcarfans.com</a><br>',' Saab Not Dead Yet - Spyker Makes New Offer'),(3716,'0','2009-12-21 15:31:35','<img src=\"http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_FmJ3CipQNPw/Sy